<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1258">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1215/423.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Mexican Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 6, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge
                            the receipt of Señor de la Cueva’s note of the 9th ultimo, by which he
                            informs the Department that your excellency holds the instructions and
                            powers necessary to take charge of the negotiations relating to the
                            final settlement of the Chamizal case, and beg to say in reply that due
                            note has been taken of Señor de la Cueva’s statement.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>